3 Months</div></div><div
class="how-to-desc"><div
class="how-to-image">
<picture>
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-start-a-restaurant-completed-800x800-20201222.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=250&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="250" height="250" alt="How to Start a Restaurant:">
</picture></div><p>A restaurant can be a fun and lucrative business venture, but it takes a lot of planning and hard work to get a new eatery off the ground. Before starting your own restaurant, you'll need a detailed business plan, a good location, a marketing strategy, and a winning menu. Follow the steps below to get your restaurant up and running.</p></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section1" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>1.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=conduct-market-research>Conduct market research.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section1-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=research-and-outline-your-concept>Research and outline your concept.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-research-and-outline-your-concept-288x288-20200824.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Research and outline your concept."></div></div><p>You may already have an idea or concept in mind for your new restaurant. Your concept should include the <strong>style</strong> of your restaurant and the <strong>food</strong> you plan to serve, including your menu. Build a clear, detailed picture. Don't be concerned if there are gaps initially. The picture will take shape and become clearer as you go.</p><p><strong>When outlining your restaurant concept:</strong></p><ul><li>Decide which demographic you want to target.</li><li>Outline the style of the service.</li><li>Describe the ambiance you want to create.</li><li>Determine what food you want to serve.</li><li>Plan your menu.</li></ul><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Examining the concepts created by other restaurants will help you develop your own. Visit their <strong>websites, social media pages, and physical locations</strong> to see how they've branded themselves. Pay attention to the food, the place settings, the atmosphere, the service, and even the color schemes.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Keep a <strong>notebook</strong> handy or use <strong>Google Docs</strong> to update your concept as you learn more and fine-tune your ideas.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section1-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=survey-consumers>Survey consumers.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-survey-consumers-288x288-2021014.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Survey consumers."></div></div><p>Doing market research for your restaurant will help you determine who your likely customers are, if there are enough of them, and how best to make them happy.</p><p>You can find consumers in places with lots of foot traffic and ask them your questions directly, or you can conduct an online survey to cast a wider net.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Create polls on Facebook, Instagram, and X formerly known as Twitter, or use free survey software to create online questionnaires.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
