</g>
</svg>
</span><p><strong>Check if your concept is feasible.</strong> Who are your prospective patrons? Will they be drawn to your concept? Will enough people with enough spending power go to your restaurant?</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Be sure to find out how many of your potential customers will visit your location and how many prefer takeout or delivery options.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section1-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=conduct-industry-research>Conduct industry research.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-do-industry-research-288x288-20200824.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Conduct industry research."></div></div><p>Look at <strong>successful restaurants</strong> similar to yours — examine them and try to decipher their secrets. Learn what customers are saying by reading their <strong>reviews</strong>. Get in touch with <strong>fellow restaurateurs</strong> to find out which restaurants the market needs or doesn't need more of.</p><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Keep abreast of industry trends and join the conversation by following your favorite eateries and chefs on social media.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>You can also get interesting ideas and insights by keeping up with restaurant shows.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>If you're struggling to connect directly with restaurant owners, try emailing them your questions. You may get more detailed responses when they reply at a time most convenient for them.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section1-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=study-your-competitors>Study your competitors.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-study-competitors-288x288-20200824.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Study your competitors."></div></div><p>Analyze your competitors to learn about their strengths and weaknesses. Find out what they're offering customers and how you can distinguish your restaurant from theirs. Look not only at what they've done right, but also examine their mistakes so that you can avoid these pitfalls.</p><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Think about ways to make customers feel safe when they visit your restaurant or order food online.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section1-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=get-people-to-sample-your-food>Get people to sample your food.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-get-people-to-sample-your-food-288x288-20200824.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Get people to sample your food."></div></div><p>Conduct <strong>taste tests</strong> with potential clients and find out what they think of your culinary creations. Friends and family work well as initial focus groups, but they can't always be relied upon to provide honest, unbiased feedback. Try setting up a stand at a local supermarket or farmer's market, or putting up advertisements for focus groups.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Prepare a list of questions that will help you get constructive feedback from your taste testers. Avoid questions such as "Do you like this?" or "How does it taste?" Instead, opt for questions like "Which of these three flavors do you prefer?" or "Which of these were too salty/sweet?"</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Pay careful attention to the body language and facial expression of the taste tester. If they come back for more samples, it's likely a good sign.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Make lots of notes during the taste tests and <strong>use negative feedback to improve your recipes</strong>. When you react badly to constructive criticism, you may discourage people from voicing their honest opinions.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section1-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=develop-a-menu-suited-to-your-target-market>Develop a menu suited to your target market.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-develop-a-menu-suited-to-your-target-market-288x288-20200824.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Develop a menu suited to your target market."></div></div><p>Use the knowledge gained from your surveys, taste tests, and other research to develop a menu that your target audience will love.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Your menu isn't set in stone. As you gain more insight into your customers' taste preferences, feel free to adjust your menu accordingly.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Now that you know your target audience, <strong>align what you have to offer them with what they have to offer you.</strong> Your concept has to meet your target market's needs. You can stick to your original concept for the sake of self-expression, but you'll have to accept the high risk of failure.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section2" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>2.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=choose-a-name-and-trademark-it>Choose a name and trademark it.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section2-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=get-ideas-from-existing-restaurants>Get ideas from existing restaurants.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-get-ideas-from-existing-restaurants-288x288-20200824.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Get ideas from existing restaurants."></div></div><p>Examine the names of existing restaurants. Find good and bad names, and try to identify why some names work well, while others don't.</p><p>Try to identify patterns in the way restaurants have been named. Do you spot any common words that are used? Write them down — they will come in handy later on.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Visit the social media pages and websites of the restaurants you research to see how the names have been used to create these brands.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Are there any eateries that changed their name at some point? If so, why?</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section2-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=name-your-business>Name your business.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-name-your-business-288x288-2020091_2023-09-26-234159_soll.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Name your business."></div></div><p>You can find several useful keywords by simply analyzing your menu, location, the ingredients used in your dishes, as well as the interests of your target market. Write down all the keywords and combine them to form restaurant names.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Use a <a
href="https://www.namesnack.com/">business name generator</a> to discover even more ideas.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section2-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=check-domain-name-availability>Check domain name availability.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-buy-the-domain-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Check domain name availability."></div></div><p>Before committing to a name, check to see whether your preferred domain name is available. If you used NameSnack to generate name ideas, the tool would have also indicated whether the corresponding domain name is available.</p><p>Alternatively, visit <a
href="https://domains.google/">domains.google</a> and search for your favorite domain name to determine its availability.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section2-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=register-your-name>Register your name.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-register-your-name-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Register your name."></div></div><p>Now that you've decided on your unique name, register it by visiting your Secretary of State's website, or your local city or county clerk's office. Requirements for registration will vary depending on your restaurant's location.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>To own the rights to your restaurant name, you can file a trademark application with the United States Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO). This <a
href="https://www.namesnack.com/guides/how-to-trademark-a-name">step-by-step guide</a> will help you do this.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section3" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>3.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=write-a-business-plan>Write a business plan.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section3-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=complete-an-overview-of-your-business-plan>Complete an overview of your business plan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-complete-an-overview-of-your-business-plan-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Complete an overview of your business plan."></div></div><p>Writing a formal business plan won't feel so daunting if you do some legwork beforehand. Jot down answers to the following questions in preparation for your business plan write-up:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Who are you?</strong>
What makes your restaurant truly special or different from the competition? Consider the overall experience as well as the individual meals on your menu.</p></li><li><p><strong>What services/solutions will you provide?</strong>
Think about how your restaurant will ultimately benefit customers. Will you offer delivery or are will yours only be a sit-down establishment?</p></li><li><p><strong>Who is your target market?</strong>
What does your ideal customer look like? Think about the customers who will most enjoy the ambiance and/or food that you serve.</p></li><li><p><strong>Who are your competitors?</strong>
How do you weigh up against other restaurants in your area?</p></li><li><p><strong>How will you market yourself?</strong>
How will you ensure that clients know about your tasty meals? What strategies will you use to create brand awareness?</p></li><li><p><strong>Who will work for you?</strong>
Describe your team. Think about all of the workers you need to hire to make a success of your restaurant.</p></li><li><p><strong>How will you make and spend money?</strong>
Provide a list of your projected income and planned expenses.</p></li><li><p><strong>What are your milestones?</strong>
Create a timeline and fill it with all of the activities you need to complete before you can start your restaurant. Include due dates and the roles of responsible staff members.</p></li></ul></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section3-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=create-your-business-plan>Create your business plan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-write-your-business-plan-800x800-20201026-2.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Create your business plan."></div></div><p>Starting a restaurant is a high-risk venture, and investors will be more approachable if you are armed with a good business plan. The document will also serve as a roadmap while you get your business up and running. Thus, it is important to draft a detailed, compelling business plan.</p><p><strong>Essentials for a restaurant business plan:</strong></p><ul><li>Executive summary.</li><li>Company description.</li><li>Marketing plan.</li><li>Operational plan.</li><li>Management plan.</li><li>Financial plan.</li><li>Appendices.</li></ul><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Download the template toward the top of this page to streamline the process of creating your business plan.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section4" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>4.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=form-your-restaurant-business>Form your restaurant business.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section4-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=create-a-legal-entity>Create a legal entity.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-create-a-legal-entity-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Create a legal entity."></div></div><p>You'll need to set up your restaurant as a legal entity for financial and professional purposes. Speak to a lawyer and a tax professional to determine which legal structure makes the most sense for your new restaurant.</p><p><strong>Some legal structures to consider include:</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Sole proprietorship</strong>: one person owns and runs the business. Sole proprietorships are great for small, low-risk businesses.</p></li><li><p><strong>Partnership</strong>: two or more people own the business, with liabilities and control divided between them. The most common types of partnerships are limited partnerships (LPs) and limited liability partnerships (LLPs).</p></li><li><p><strong>C corporation</strong>: a separate legal entity that provides maximum protection from personal liability. C corporations can continue undisturbed when shareholders leave or sell their shares but may be subject to double taxation.</p></li><li><p><strong>S corporation</strong>: a unique type of corporation that's not subject to double taxation. Like C corporations, S corporations are regarded as distinct legal entities. However, they must meet <a
href="https://www.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/s-corporations">specific criteria</a>.</p></li><li><p><strong>Limited liability company (LLC)</strong>: a cross between a corporation and a partnership. This structure allows members to protect their personal assets and is suitable for medium to high-risk businesses.</p></li></ul><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>If you decide to register as an LLC, it is advisable to create an <strong>operating agreement</strong>. In fact, this may be a requirement in your state, so make sure to visit your Secretary of State website to double-check.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>For more information about legal structures suited to restaurants, you can approach the <a
href="https://restaurant.org/">National Restaurant Association</a> or your local state restaurant association.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section4-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=obtain-an-employer-identification-number>Obtain an Employer Identification Number (EIN).</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-obtain-en-employer-identification-number-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Obtain an Employer Identification Number (EIN)."></div></div><p>You'll probably have a team running your restaurant, so you'll need to <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-apply-for-an-ein">apply for an Employer Identification Number (EIN)</a> for tax purposes. This <a
href="https://www.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/do-you-need-an-ein">may even be a requirement</a> if you'll be operating your restaurant single-handedly.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section4-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=open-a-business-bank-account>Open a business bank account.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-open-a-business-bank-account-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Open a business bank account."></div></div><p>A business bank account will help separate your business and personal finances, simplify your tax preparation, offer a sense of credibility, and help you build a good relationship with your bank.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section4-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=apply-for-licenses-and-permits>Apply for licenses and permits.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-licenses-and-permits-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Apply for licenses and permits."></div></div><p>There are some basic licenses and permits that all restaurants require, and others that may not apply to you. <a
href="#restaurant-licensing-requirements">Discover which licenses and permits you need</a> and obtain these before you open your restaurant.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section4-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=purchase-insurance>Purchase insurance.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-purchase-insurance-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Purchase insurance."></div></div><p>Ensure that injuries, accidents, and similar phenomena are covered so that you, your workers, customers, and business are protected.</p><p><strong>Consider purchasing the following types of insurance:</strong></p><ul><li>Commercial general liability insurance.</li><li>Commercial auto insurance.</li><li>Workers' compensation insurance.</li><li>Commercial umbrella insurance.</li></ul><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Before signing up with an insurance company, compare quotes and consult an independent insurance agent.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>To save money, take out multiple insurance policies with the same provider and <strong>bundle them</strong>.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section5" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>5.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=decide-on-a-location>Decide on a location.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section5-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=research-local-areas>Research local areas.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-research-local-areas-288x288-20201222.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Research local areas."></div></div><p>Look at a few different areas where you could set up your restaurant. They should be safe, well-placed, and near your target market, with minimal competition.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Shop around and compare quotes before making the final decision.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section5-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=make-sure-you-have-ample-parking>Make sure you have ample parking.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-make-sure-you-have-ample-parking-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Make sure you have ample parking."></div></div><p>To determine your parking ratio — how many parking spots you have relative to the square footage of your restaurant — you'll need to perform some calculations.</p><p>Take, for example, a restaurant with 400 parking spots that's 50,000 square feet. The calculation to determine the parking ratio is 400 divided by 50. The result is eight parking spaces per 1,000 square feet.</p><p>You could also estimate how many patrons you would expect on your busiest day. Assume each one arrived in their own vehicle. That is how much parking you'll need.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Each city has different rules and regulations regarding parking. You'll need to familiarize yourself with these before you choose your location.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section6" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>6.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=secure-financing>Secure financing.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section6-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=contact-the-national-restaurant-association>Contact the National Restaurant Association.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-contact-the-national-restaurant-association-288x288-20201223.jpg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Contact the National Restaurant Association."></div></div><p>Get in touch with the National Restaurant Association and your local state restaurant association for advice. These bodies can offer guidance on how to secure financing for your restaurant.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section6-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=apply-for-a-loan>Apply for a loan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-a-loan-288x288-20200728_2023-09-26-235358_prmr.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Apply for a loan."></div></div><p>Approach a bank to apply for a small business loan. Be prepared and professional, and make sure you furnish the bank with all the required documentation. Remember to bring your detailed business plan along, too.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Be sure to shop around for the most favorable repayment terms before you commit to anything.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section6-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=get-an-sba-loan>Get an SBA loan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-an-sba-loan-288x288-20200820_2023-09-26-235447_ooms.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Get an SBA loan."></div></div><p>The U.S. Small Business Administration (SBA) offers loans with longer repayment periods, lower interest rates, and smaller down payments compared to conventional loans. You can <a
href="https://www.sba.gov/funding-programs/loans/lender-match">find a suitable lender</a> and get the process started in just two days.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section6-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=obtain-a-business-credit-card>Obtain a business credit card.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-obtain-a-business-credit-card-800x800-20201029.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Obtain a business credit card."></div></div><p>A business credit card can give you financial flexibility and will help keep your business and personal finances separate. They are easier to apply for than loans and can help you build a good credit score.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Shop around before applying for a business credit card, and compare reward programs before making a final decision. Many business credit cards offer points that can be converted to cash rewards and/or travel credit.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section6-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=find-investors>Find investors.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-get-investors-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Find investors."></div></div><p>Network until you find your investor(s). Reach out to family and friends who have the capital to invest in your venture. You can also try to secure an <strong>angel investor</strong> — they'll have some interest in the viability of the venture.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section6-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=try-crowdfunding>Try crowdfunding.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-try-crowdfunding-288x288-2020107.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Try crowdfunding."></div></div><p>Once you get your brand out there, you can try to get crowdfunding through sites such as FoodStart, Kickstarter, Indiegogo, and GoFundMe.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section6-step7" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.7&nbsp;</span><h4 id=strike-a-deal-with-your-landlord>Strike a deal with your landlord.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-strike-a-deal-with-your-landlord-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Strike a deal with your landlord."></div></div><p>Ask your landlord for <strong>reduced rent in exchange for shares in your restaurant.</strong> Consider this option once you secure premises for your restaurant.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section6-step8" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.8&nbsp;</span><h4 id=use-your-own-money>Use your own money.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-use-your-own-money-288x288-20200821_2023-09-26-235840_saje.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Use your own money."></div></div><p>If you've saved up to open your dream restaurant, using your own money is a great way to avoid debt and overspending. This may also allow you to maintain full control of your business.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>If you have enough savings to cover your startup capital, your restaurant may be up and running sooner than expected.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Even if you don't have all the funds required to get your restaurant off the ground, using your savings can still minimize your overall liabilities.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>It is important to note how much you might earn. <a
href="https://www.payscale.com/research/US/Job=Owner_%2F_Operator%2C_Restaurant/Salary">Research</a> shows that the average restaurant owner earns around $65,000 per year. However, there is considerable variation from about $33,000 to $144,000.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section7" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>7.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=secure-and-prepare-your-space>Secure and prepare your space.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section7-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=make-a-list-of-everything-you-039-ll-need-and-compare-prices>Make a list of everything you&#039;ll need and compare prices.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-make-a-list-of-everything-youll-need-and-compare-prices-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Make a list of everything you&#039;ll need and compare prices."></div></div><p>To get an idea of what it is going to cost you to open your restaurant and what it will take to get it off the ground, make a list of what you’ll need to purchase and compare prices before committing to anything.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Refer back to your business plan where you would have outlined your equipment and inventory requirements, as well as estimated costs thereof.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section7-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=secure-premises>Secure premises.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-secure-premises-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Secure premises."></div></div><p>There are many factors to consider when choosing premises for your restaurant, and at this stage, you will still be looking around to get an idea of what is available. Contact commercial real estate brokers in your area to help you find the perfect spot.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Consider renting kitchen space from a food incubator or an incubator program, or starting a food truck, pop-up restaurant, or ghost kitchen. A pop-up restaurant or supper club can be operated from factory spaces, private homes, and festivals.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section7-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=complete-shopfitting>Complete shopfitting.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-complete-shopfitting-288x288-20200825-2.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Complete shopfitting."></div></div><p>Depending on your budget, you can either hire a shopfitting firm, a consultant, or do the work yourself with help from friends and family.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p><strong>Shop around</strong> for furniture to find the best deals. Auctions are a good place to source almost new furniture. Depending on your budget and the style of your restaurant, you can also shop around for more worn pieces.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Shopfitting costs range from $300.00 to $500.00 per square foot for a kitchen, and $150.00 to $300.00 per square foot for a dining room.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section7-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=purchase-small-appliances-utensils-and-more>Purchase small appliances, utensils, and more.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-purchase-small-appliances-utensils-and-more-800x800-20201026.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Purchase small appliances, utensils, and more."></div></div><p>There are many suppliers of small appliances, some of which cater to the restaurant industry, specifically. Shop around for the best deals.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section7-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=purchase-electronic-equipment>Purchase electronic equipment.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-purchase-electronic-equipment-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Purchase electronic equipment."></div></div><p>You may need a restaurant point of sale (POS) system, as well as a computer to take bookings and communicate with patrons, suppliers, and others via email. You may also want to purchase a few television sets if you're hoping to attract sports fans.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section7-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=purchase-office-equipment-and-basic-office-furniture>Purchase office equipment and basic office furniture.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-office-equipment-and-basic-office-furniture-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Purchase office equipment and basic office furniture."></div></div><p>You'll need some basic office furniture for your back office or little corner where you'll do your restaurant's admin and cash-outs. There are many well-established suppliers of office furniture and equipment to choose from.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section7-step7" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.7&nbsp;</span><h4 id=purchase-uniforms>Purchase uniforms.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-uniforms-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Purchase uniforms."></div></div><p>These can be sourced from a company that specializes in restaurant uniforms. Alternatively, you could agree on a specific outfit that all staff will wear — for instance, blue jeans and white T-shirts.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Refer to our table to discover the <a
href="#restaurant-uniform-prices">prices of restaurant uniforms</a>.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section7-step8" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.8&nbsp;</span><h4 id=purchase-consumables>Purchase consumables.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-consumables-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Purchase consumables."></div></div><p>You will need to shop around for companies that best meet your needs for a range of supplies, such as food and beverages. You won't be able to get all your supplies from one company, so be prepared to deal with a number of suppliers with whom you will build relationships over time.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section8" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>8.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=build-your-team>Build your team.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section8-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=write-compelling-job-descriptions>Write compelling job descriptions.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-write-compelling-job-descriptions-288x288-2020107.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Write compelling job descriptions."></div></div><p>Create enticing job descriptions and post them on local job boards and social media.</p><p><strong>Some positions you may want to fill at your restaurant include:</strong></p><ul><li>Restaurant manager.</li><li>Executive chef.</li><li>Sous chef.</li><li>Line cook.</li><li>Food preparation worker.</li><li>Barista.</li><li>Busser.</li><li>Food server.</li><li>Food runner.</li><li>Host.</li></ul></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section8-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=identify-and-interview-the-best-candidates>Identify and interview the best candidates.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-identify-and-interview-the-best-candidates-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Identify and interview the best candidates."></div></div><p>Consider using recruitment and resume parsing software, as well as staffing agencies, to identify the best candidates for your vacancies. Thereafter, conduct interviews and send out job offers.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Look for individuals who can work in fast-paced, high-pressure environments, and who don't mind working late nights and weekends.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p><strong>Implement paid tryouts.</strong> Don't make a final decision right away; test the water with paid tryouts. This is a great way to evaluate applicants before making permanent additions to your team.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section8-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=train-your-team>Train your team.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-train-your-team-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Train your team."></div></div><p>Ensure that all workers are familiar with health and workplace safety policies, that they know how to use the necessary equipment, and that the front of house staff are well versed in customer service.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Once you have built your team and need more hands, spread the word about available positions. Start by asking your staff to let their friends and family know about the vacancies.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section9" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>9.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=market-your-restaurant>Market your restaurant.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section9-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>9.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=create-a-website>Create a website.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-create-a-website-or-blog-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Create a website."></div></div><p>This is a great way to showcase your offerings while making your restaurant look like a professional business. You may want to add features to your website that enable customers to order ahead.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section9-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>9.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=set-up-social-media-accounts>Set up social media accounts.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-set-up-social-media-accounts-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Set up social media accounts."></div></div><p>A social media presence will encourage potential clients to engage with your brand, see and share upcoming specials, and check in virtually when they visit your restaurant.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Get users to spread the word about your new restaurant by creating competitions where, for example, pages are liked, promotional posts are shared, and other users are tagged in the comments section.</p></div><div
