</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Consider hiring a professional to help you.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section9-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>9.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=be-a-walking-talking-billboard>Be a walking, talking billboard.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-do-it-yourself-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Be a walking, talking billboard."></div></div><p>Tell people about your restaurant and what you've got to offer wherever you go. Having your business name and logo printed on uniforms, work and/or personal vehicles, and stationery is another way to get the word out about your new restaurant.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section10" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>10.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=complete-the-final-checks-before-your-grand-opening>Complete the final checks before your grand opening.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section10-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=double-check-your-inventory>Double-check your inventory.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-double-check-inventory-288x288-20200825.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Double-check your inventory."></div></div><p>Ensure that you have everything you need for a smooth grand opening. Tick the items off on a list and make the necessary purchases if anything has been overlooked.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-restaurant-section10-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=have-a-dress-rehearsal>Have a dress rehearsal.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-have-a-dress-rehearsal-288x288-2021014.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Have a dress rehearsal."></div></div><p>Host a soft opening where a few customers are allowed a sneak peek at your menu and get to experience your new restaurant in an intimate setting. Prepare some of your signature dishes and get feedback from your diners before the grand opening.</p><p>If your budget allows, you can offer discounted meals or free food at your soft opening. However, if you have limited funds, be sure to offer a complimentary drink or some other token of appreciation to your guests.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
