class="block block-rank-table"><h2 id=cost-of-starting-a-restaurant>Cost of Starting a Restaurant:</h2><div
class="table-wrapper"><div
class="table-responsive"><table
class="table"><tbody><tr><th><p>Restaurant Type</p></th><th><p>Price</p></th></tr><tr><td><p>Food Truck</p></td><td><p>$15,000-$100,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Diner</p></td><td><p>$200,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fast-Food Franchise</p></td><td><p>$10,000-$2.5 million</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div><div
class="block block-rank-table"><h2 id=restaurant-uniform-prices>Restaurant Uniform Prices:</h2><div
class="table-wrapper"><div
class="table-responsive"><table
class="table"><tbody><tr><th><p>Item</p></th><th><p>Price</p></th></tr><tr><td><p>Apron</p></td><td><p>$3.50-$16.95</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Shirt</p></td><td><p>$4.95-$32.80</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Pants</p></td><td><p>$16.95-$29.60</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Skirt</p></td><td><p>Approx. $36.00</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div><div
class="block block-rank-table"><h2 id=restaurant-licensing-requirements>Restaurant Licensing Requirements:</h2><div
class="table-wrapper"><div
class="table-responsive"><table
class="table"><tbody><tr><th><p>License Type*</p></th><th><p>Details</p></th></tr><tr><td><p>Business License</p></td><td><p>A business license authorizes your business to operate. You need to apply for your business license with the city or state where you plan on opening your restaurant. The process of obtaining a business license depends on the state in which your business is located and the nature of your business.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Certificate of Occupancy</p></td><td><p>This is required to verify that your building is safe for your staff and customers. It will be issued by local authorities in the town or city where your restaurant is based.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Food Service License</p></td><td><p>This will permit you to sell food. Contact the applicable local authorities to inquire about applying for a food license.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Liquor License</p></td><td><p>Liquor laws vary between states. Check these as soon as possible to estimate the applicable costs, as well as how long it will take to be issued a liquor license.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sign Permit</p></td><td><p>Before you erect signage for your restaurant, you may need a sign permit from your local authority. A sign permit will prescribe the dimensions of your signage and where you are allowed to erect it.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Music License</p></td><td><p>Even if you pay for a streaming service, you still need to pay performing rights organizations (PROs) to play copyrighted music in your restaurant. You can pay an annual blanket music license fee with one of the three main PROs in the U.S.: ASCAP, BMI, or SESAC. Note that you may face penalties of between $750 and $30,000 if you do not pay.</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div><div
class="block"><p>*This is not an exhaustive list. You may need to obtain additional licenses and permits for your restaurant.</p></div><div
